From: Frogging-Family
From: damachine <damachin3@proton.me>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 21:14:59 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] nvidia open-kernel: dsc/dp fixes

Patches against the latest NVIDIA open-gpu-kernel-modules release:
- src/common/displayport/src/dp_wardatabase.cpp: add Bigscreen Beyond VR
  headset (ManufID 0x2709, ProdID 0x1234) to DP WAR database (4 lanes HBR2)
- src/common/modeset/timing/nvt_dsc_pps.c: correct DSC RC parameter tables
  to match VESA DSC 1.1 (9 fixes in minqp444_8b, maxqp444_8b, ofs_und8)

Signed-off-by: damachine <damachin3@proton.me>

---
 src/common/displayport/src/dp_wardatabase.cpp | 13 +++++++++++++
 src/common/modeset/timing/nvt_dsc_pps.c       | 18 +++++++++---------
 2 files changed, 22 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)
diff --git a/src/common/displayport/src/dp_wardatabase.cpp b/src/common/displayport/src/dp_wardatabase.cpp
index 74daf1e..4fafb5f 100644
--- a/src/common/displayport/src/dp_wardatabase.cpp
+++ b/src/common/displayport/src/dp_wardatabase.cpp
@@ -547,6 +547,19 @@ void Edid::applyEdidWorkArounds(NvU32 warFlag, const DpMonitorDenylistData *pDen
             }
             break;
 
+        // Bigscreen Beyond VR headset
+        case 0x2709:
+            if (ProductID == 0x1234)
+            {
+                //
+                // The Bigscreen Beyond connects via a link box (DP -> optical).
+                // Force 4 lanes HBR2 to ensure sufficient bandwidth.
+                //
+                this->WARFlags.forceMaxLinkConfig = true;
+                DP_PRINTF(DP_NOTICE, "DP-WAR> Force maximum link config for Bigscreen Beyond VR headset.");
+            }
+            break;
+
         // CMN
         case 0xAE0D:
             if (ProductID == 0x1747)
